The paper deals with the security of cyber-physical systems (CPSs) and proposes a technique for testing their defences against network attacks. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed technique involves the use of machine learning models and metaheuristic search algorithms, which suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the implementation of the technique on real-world CPS testbeds, which involves software engineering (cs.SE) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
